    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "THE RED CARPET",
      "Beverages\nWHISKIES\nBOURBON\nSCOTCH\nCANADIAN\nTENNESSEE\nCOCKTAILS\nUNITED'S VERY DRY MARTINI\n(GIN OR VODKA)\nOLD FASHIONED\nMANHATTAN\nDAIQUIRI\nBLOODY MARY\nSPANISH SHERRY\nGIN\nVODKA\nWINES\nCHAMPAGNE (Split)\nRED WINE (Split)\nLIQUEURS\nBENEDICTINE AND BRANDY\nDRAMBUIE\nONE DOLLAR FACH_LIMIT TWO\n* **\nDELD\nFIETY CENTS FACH\nSALTED NUTS\nMinors Will Not Be Served Liquor.\nMenu\nSLICED EGG AND TOMATO SALAD\nWITH SHRIMP\nLORENZO DRESSING\nBROILED FILET MIGNON, BERCY SAUCE\nChoice steer beef tenderloin with the Chef's special sauce.\nDUCHESSE POTATOES\nGREEN PEAS WITH PEARL ONIONS\nOR\nSHORT RIBS OF BEEF\nBUTTERED EGG NOODLES\nFRENCH CUT GREEN BEANS\nSAN FRANCISCO SOUR DOUGH ROLL\nROYAL HAWAIIAN COUPE\nCOFFEE\nTEA\nMILK\nRED WINE AND CHAMPAGNE SPLITS ARE\nAVAILABLE WITH MEAL SERVICE. $1.00 EACH.\nThis menu prepared in United Air Lines Flight Kitchen\nat Chicago—O'Hare International Airport, Edwin Wirz, Chef.\nMember, Illinois Executive Chefs' Association\nMember, American Culinary Federation"
    ],
